+#### AI Work Step Event Schema
+
+AI work steps use the canonical event envelope with `payload.kind` set to
+`ai-work-step`. They are designed to be read as an ordered step list by CLI,
+HTTP API, JSONL readers, and AI agents without a dedicated timeline UI.
+
+```json
+{
+  "schemaVersion": 1,
+  "protocol": "lux.ai.action_log.v1",
+  "id": "ai-step-apply-patch-0003",
+  "timestampUtc": "2026-05-04T00:00:03.0000000Z",
+  "projectPath": "/path/to/unity-project",
+  "source": "codex",
+  "actor": "codex",
+  "category": "ai-action-log",
+  "type": "tool.apply_patch.completed",
+  "summary": "Applied a patch to the AI action log tests.",
+  "message": "Applied a patch to the AI action log tests.",
+  "status": "completed",
+  "tool": "apply_patch",
+  "sessionId": "codex-session-1",
+  "correlationId": "corr-ai-step-1",
+  "redactionMetadata": {
+    "policyVersion": "lux.redaction.v1",
+    "applied": true,
+    "redactedCount": 1,
+    "redactedFields": ["payload.content.inputSummary"],
+    "redactionClasses": ["credential"]
+  },
+  "payload": {
+    "kind": "ai-work-step",
+    "eventType": "tool.apply_patch.completed",
+    "stepName": "apply_patch",
+    "status": "completed",
+    "summary": "Applied a patch to the AI action log tests.",
+    "ordering": {
+      "sequence": 3,
+      "parentSequence": 2,
+      "previousEventId": "ai-step-read-files-0002",
+      "groupId": "phase6-ac5"
+    },
+    "timestamps": {
+      "recordedAtUtc": "2026-05-04T00:00:03.0000000Z",
+      "startedAtUtc": "2026-05-04T00:00:02.0000000Z",
+      "completedAtUtc": "2026-05-04T00:00:03.0000000Z",
+      "durationMs": 1000
+    },
+    "tool": {
+      "name": "apply_patch",
+      "action": "edit",
+      "invocationId": "tool-call-3",
+      "exitCode": 0
+    },
+    "action": {
+      "name": "modify-file",
+      "target": "LuxEditorTests/Editor/LuxAiActionLogTests.cs",
+      "result": "updated"
+    },
+    "content": {
+      "summary": "Applied a patch to the AI action log tests.",
+      "inputSummary": "[REDACTED]",
+      "outputSummary": "Patch applied cleanly."
+    },
+    "redactionMetadata": {
+      "policyVersion": "lux.redaction.v1",
+      "applied": true,
+      "redactedCount": 1,
+      "redactedFields": ["payload.content.inputSummary"],
+      "redactionClasses": ["credential"]
+    },
+    "attributes": {
+      "changedFiles": ["LuxEditorTests/Editor/LuxAiActionLogTests.cs"],
+      "diagnosticCount": 0
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Required AI work-step fields:
+
+| Field | Type | Description |
+| :--- | :--- | :--- |
+| `type` / `payload.eventType` | string | Stable step event name, for example `ai.step.started`, `ai.step.completed`, or `tool.apply_patch.completed`. |
+| `status` / `payload.status` | string | Step state: `queued`, `started`, `in-progress`, `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`, `skipped`, or `blocked`. |
+| `summary` / `payload.summary` | string | Redacted one-line step summary for compact readers. |
+| `payload.stepName` | string | Human-readable stable step name such as `inspect-files`, `apply_patch`, `cargo-test`, or `unity-smoke-test`. |
+| `payload.ordering.sequence` | number | Monotonic sequence within the producer session or correlation group. Readers sort by `timestampUtc`, then `sequence`, then JSONL line number when present. |
+| `payload.timestamps.recordedAtUtc` | string | UTC timestamp when the log record was emitted. Should match top-level `timestampUtc` unless replaying imported records. |
+| `payload.tool.name` | string | Tool, skill, or command surface used for the step. |
+| `payload.tool.action` | string | Tool/action verb such as `read`, `edit`, `test`, `run-command`, `http-read`, or `unity-event`. |
+| `payload.action.name` | string | Workflow-level action name independent of the concrete tool. |
+| `payload.content.summary` | string | Redacted summarized content. Do not store full prompts, source files, logs, or gameplay state here. |
+| `redactionMetadata` | object | Top-level redaction metadata for persisted and returned event data. |
+| `payload.redactionMetadata` | object | Payload-local copy so readers that consume only `payload` still know whether summaries and tool metadata were redacted. |
+
+Optional fields such as `parentSequence`, `previousEventId`, `groupId`,
+`startedAtUtc`, `completedAtUtc`, `durationMs`, `tool.invocationId`,
+`tool.exitCode`, `action.target`, `action.result`, `content.inputSummary`,
+`content.outputSummary`, `content.errorSummary`, and `attributes` are retained
+when useful and redacted before persistence, API responses, and broadcasts.
+
